Created attachment 147535
Patch to update the Makefile, distinfo and pkg-descr

astro/wmmoonclock has been marked as BROKEN due to no available distfiles. As it turns out, there are upstream distfiles, it's just that MASTER_SITES is incorrect. Moreover, this port is currently orphaned and I volunteer to take maintainership.

The attached patch addresses the following:
* removal of BROKEN;
* corrected MASTER_SITES including new maitainer's mirror;
* updated distinfo [1];
* addition of LICENSE specification;
* new maintainer
* slight grammar change in pkg-descr;
* addition of WWW to pkg-descr.

The new port has been checked with portlint -AC and (links to) Redports build logs for several architectures are (read: should be) available at
http://www.skysmurf.nl/comp/FreeBSD/redports/wmmoonclock-2014092100.html
although it's the first time I've use Redports so I hope the links work.

Ad [1]: The distfile on distcache is significantly larger than the upstream tarball although I can not discern any difference in content.The new distinfo reflects the upstream tarball and that's the one I'm mirroring at the moment.
